.START 

Magma Copper Co. said it assigned to Canyon Resources Corp. Magma's option to buy Addwest Gold Inc., a unit of Addington Resources Inc. 

Canyon said it exercised the option and expects to complete the purchase by Dec. 31, subject to financing for the $33 million transaction. 

Magma Copper said the agreement calls for it to receive from Canyon the $500,000 it paid for the option in August plus about $250,000 in related expenses. 

Addwest Gold holds a 60% interest in the Kendall gold mine in Montana as well as various properties in that state and in California. 

Magma, based in San Manuel, Ariz.; Addington Resources, Ashland, Ky.; and Canyon, Golden, Colo., are all mining companies.
Magma's stock fell 12.5 cents Friday to close at $6.50 a share in American Stock Exchange composite trading. 

Addington rose 50 cents to $20.75 a share in national over-the-counter trading. 

